reviews.text: The lunch set is fantastic! Especially the truffle fries, recommend and will again soon.

Service was alright. Ordered a glass of white, first time the glass and the staff was willing to give me another glass when i asked. The food was below average. I ordered black truffle risotto with goose liver. It was too oily. There was a sea of oil floating at the periphery of the plate! Goose liver was just alright, cannot expect that much with such price

One of the best places for pasta! I personally think that their pasta are more outstanding than their pizza. Book in advance since the shop is relatively small (especially during the weekends it’s always full).

The mushroom soup is brilliant. The ingredients are very plentiful. The other foods are also very delicious. The staffs are very initiative and the chef is very cheerful. It is the best restaurant I've ever been. I'll visit there again.

Pizza is good but steak not too good

reviews.text: 第一次嚟，試咗唔係好多嘢，但印象幾深刻。個drumstick一定要試，香港好少食到肉質咁嫩嘅雞，仲要炸得啱啱好，咬落去裏面有肉汁咇出嚟。pizza都唔錯，可以叫多幾款試試。嗰度有賣果醋，有蘋果同蜜桃味，兩隻都好飲，同啲菜式幾夾，建議叫返兩三支。
The lunch set is fantastic! Especially the truffle fries, recommend and will again soon.

Service was alright. Ordered a glass of white, first time the glass and the staff was willing to give me another glass when i asked. The food was below average. I ordered black truffle risotto with goose liver. It was too oily. There was a sea of oil floating at the periphery of the plate! Goose liver was just alright, cannot expect that much with such price
價位高，份量少，幸好食物好吃
餐廳不算大，但食物不錯

This was a great area for sightseeing and taking a walk. There are an amazing assortment of restaurants and stores along the way. We ate at a little hole in the wall Vietnamese restaurant that was absolutely awesome.

This neighbourhood has a couple of murals that are well known to tourists, (ex. The one pictured here as well as the brooklyn mural). It is a great place for taking photos; however, I would recommend for future visitors to arrive earlier to take pictures (11:30 am latest) because it will get pretty crowded at the murals after noon.

Good area in Hong Kong overall to go out and chill -whether you prefer that be over good food, drinks or both. Some places here also show sports games, and there are plenty of cuisines represented. Do prepare to spend a bit more, and getting around in the crowd here can be tiring, or nearly impossible if you have mobility restrictions.
Such a great vibe. Lots of great bars. Very western environment not what you would imagine HK to be like.
Soho is a little upscale part of LKF central. Most Western locals go here. You will have fun!
